MOSELLE WINES

These lovely wines are easily digested, wholesome and constitute an ideal luncheon wnie, thanks to their low alcoholic content and natural dryness. They are distinguished by a delightfully fresh pleasant flavor which is, at the same time, stimulating. Their sprightly bouquet has been compared to the “scent of primroses growing on a bank of damp, mossy earth.” The Riesling grape is at once apparent, in all its purity.
